subSubSection.paragraph:
Genitalia
: Uncus apically broad, plate-like, partially bifurcated, latero-distally extended and acute; Socii robust, outwardly curved, extending beyond half-length of uncus, small basal process present; tegumen robust, elongated, more or less straight; valva crescent-shaped, ventrally curved, costal margin highly convex, basal part well sclerotized with irregular minute dentations; juxta trapezoidal with dorso-lateral slender process on each side; vinculum broad, well sclerotized, u-shaped; saccus strongly reduced (
Fig. 10
); aedeagus stout, distal half highly curved with a large, broad subapical spine and a minute apical spine; vesica slightly sclerotized at its distal end (
Fig. 12
).
